From 5dbb2fd1a4c7da470dcd261fa803150fc1f19e1b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lids Labs <55252374+lidslabs@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 14:52:18 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 23/24] hls: remove the force-SDR-clients lever (superseded by
 the SDR ladder)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The LIDSLABS_FORCE_SDR_CLIENTS lever (v0.3.2 patches 0011 + 0014) forced
listed AVPlayer-family clients (Neptune AV) to an HDR->SDR tonemap because
they black-screened on the HDR-over-HLS master. The real cause was the
master advertising a single VIDEO-RANGE=PQ variant; AVPlayer refuses an
HDR-only ladder. The HDR-passthrough master now carries an H.264 SDR
companion rung (patch 0020), so AVPlayer clients start on the SDR rung and
switch up to HDR themselves — Swiftfin and Neptune AV both verified, and
Moonfin's mpv EDR washout (the other force-SDR use) was fixed upstream and
now renders HDR10 correctly on device.

With no client left needing it, remove:
  - the PlaybackInfo force-SDR CodecProfile prepend and its gate,
  - the force-SDR arm of the delivered-range PlaybackInfo rewrite (the
    HDR-passthrough arm stays),
  - the 'moonfin' arm of LidslabsClientMatches (added solely for this lever).

Kept: the EncodingHelper 'honor an explicit SDR request' gate (now backs
the SDR-ladder rung), the shared LidslabsClientMatches matcher (still used
by the forced-HEVC lever), and LidslabsClearDoViDescriptors. Comments at
the touched sites updated to reflect the SDR-ladder resolution.
